pulse_actions is a tool that listens to various pulse exchanges/topics and takes actions accordingly.

Here's the workflow:
https://wiki.mozilla.org/Auto-tools/Projects/Pulse_actions#Workflow

On Treeherder developers can request various actions. Some of those are:
* backfill a job to the last known good
* add new jobs to pushes
* add all missing jobs for a revision
* add talos jobs

The current implementation uses TC/BBB to schedule graphs that will schedule the necessary builds and tests for those requests.
It also schedule some jobs through Buildapi when TC/BBB cannot be used.
